<p>A simpler modern example is a home office. In 2020–2022, a $2,500 setup for a remote worker often had a real return: preserved employment, higher productivity, and lower commuting costs. The same $2,500 spent on trend-driven gadgets bought near peak pandemic prices often produced little beyond short-lived excitement and poor resale.</p>
